# Walkthrough: Settings Page Redesign + File Preview Loading

## Changes Made

### 1. Backend — Session Enrichment & APIs

#### [NEW] [parseUserAgent.js](file:///c:/Users/rudra/Desktop/storageApp/backend/utils/parseUserAgent.js)
- Simple UA parser that extracts browser name, OS, and device type (desktop/mobile/tablet) without external libraries.

#### [MODIFY] [authController.js](file:///c:/Users/rudra/Desktop/storageApp/backend/controller/authController.js)
- **Session data enrichment**: All session creation points (login, Google login for existing users, Google login for new users) now store `userAgent` and `createdAt` timestamp alongside `userId` in the Redis hash.
- **Session limit increased**: Max concurrent sessions changed from 2 → 3, with proper oldest-session eviction based on `createdAt`.
- **`getSessions`**: New controller that returns all active sessions for the current user with parsed device info.
- **`logoutSession`**: New controller that terminates a specific session (verifies it belongs to the requesting user).

#### [MODIFY] [authRoutes.js](file:///c:/Users/rudra/Desktop/storageApp/backend/routes/authRoutes.js)
- Added `GET /auth/sessions` and `DELETE /auth/sessions/:sessionId` routes.

